The paper discusses the behavior of content publishers in BitTorrent, which involves aspects of computer security (cs.CR) due to the presence of fake files and malware, digital libraries (cs.DL) as BitTorrent is a popular P2P content delivery application, social networks (cs.SI) as the study examines the behavior of individual users sharing content with others, multimedia (cs.MM) as the content shared can be of various types, and information retrieval (cs.IR) as the study involves identifying and analyzing the behavior of content publishers.
